.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-info 1  "info " 
.SH NAME
info \- Print a summary of a WebP file (size, alpha, metadata, animation)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBinfo\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print a summary of a WebP file (size, alpha, metadata, animation)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Print the report as JSON instead of text.

One object, with a `schema` field to pin. Nothing is decoded either way, so this is cheap on any size of file.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
[\fIINPUT\fR] [default: \-]
Input `.webp` file; `\-` (the default) reads stdin
